<p>Assume an investor starts from zero, contributes <strong>€1,000 per month</strong> (€12,000 per year), and earns a long-run average return of <strong>6% annually</strong>. That is a sensible, non-heroic assumption for a diversified portfolio. No leverage, no stock-picking miracle, no perfect market timing.</p>
